  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ecosan in Bugesera DWA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in Bugesera District, in the Eastern Province of Rwanda.  It is aimed at improving sanitation in poor households within communal rural villages, through the use of Ecological Sanitation toilets commonly known as EcoSan.   It is projected that WaterAid will reach 1,600 direct users from 200 households within year one, with the potential for doubling this reach in subsequent years. Other target groups will be 600 people from the supported households who will be trained on appropriate hygiene behaviours to enhance the use of the EcoSan toilets, and 50 local technicians (masons) who will be trained on the construction and use of this new sanitation technology. This is a one year project. The demonstration work on EcoSan will be done in two model villages of Bugesera District from which the learning and replication of the technology will take place, with hope to become a formally endorsed technology to be used in communal villages at district level.</narrative>
  </description>
